bout 1180":"circa 1180","abt. 1214":"circa 1214","1164":"1164","1120":"1120","1252":"1252","1130":"1130","1182":"1182","1160":"1160","1180":"1180","abt. 1180":"circa 1180","1214":"1214","1158":"1158","1200":"1200","1155":"1155","Abt 1182":"circa 1182","of,, Roxburgh, Scotland":"Roxburghshire, Schotland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Scotland":"Schotland","Roxburghshire, Scotland":"Roxburghshire, Schotland"},"en":{"abt. 1158–abt. 1214":"about 1158–about 1214","1155–Male":"1155–Deceased","1158–1214":"1158–1214","1160–1200":"1160–1200","1155–1180":"1155–1180","1180–1252":"1180–1252","1182–Male":"1182–Deceased","1120–Male":"1120–Deceased","1130–Female":"1130–Deceased","abt. 1158":"about 1158","about 1180":"about 1180","abt. 1214":"about 1214","1164":"1164","1120":"1120","1252":"1252","1130":"1130","1182":"1182","1160":"1160","1180":"1180","abt. 1180":"about 1180","1214":"1214","1158":"1158","1200":"1200","1155":"1155","Abt 1182":"about 1182","of,, Roxburgh, Scotland":"Roxburghshire, Scotland, United Kingdom","Scotland":"Scotland","Roxburghshire, Scotland":"Roxburghshire, Scotland","nameMeanings":[{"name":"de","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Rutherfurd","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Scottish and northern English: habitational name from Rutherford in Maxton (Roxburghshire), apparently named with Old English <i>hrīther</i>, <i>hrȳther</i> ‘ox’ + <i>ford</i> ‘ford’, though a British Celtic origin of the type <i>ro-</i> ‘great’ + <i>dubr-</i> ‘water, river’ is also possible for the first element. Places named <i>Rutherford</i> in West Linton (West Lothian) and Barningham (North Yorkshire) are less likely sources of the name."],"variants":[{"name":"Reliford","meanings":["Altered form of English   Rutherford  . Its bearers are mainly African Americans. Compare   Relaford  ,   Releford  ,   Relford  ."]},{"name":"Retherford","meanings":["Altered form of English   Rutherford  ."]}]},{"name":"Gregory","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Via Latin <i>Gregorius</i> from the post-classical Greek name <i>Gregōrios</i> ‘watchful’ (a derivative of <i>gregōrein</i> ‘to watch, be vigilant’). The name was a very popular one among the early Christians, who were mindful of the injunction ‘be sober, be vigilant’ (1 Peter 5:8). It was borne by a number of early saints. The most important, in honour of whom the name was often bestowed from medieval times onwards, were Gregory of Nazianzen (  <i>c.</i>329–90 ), Gregory of Nyssa (  d. <i>c.</i>395 ), Gregory of Tours (  538–94 ), and  Pope Gregory the Great  (  <i>c.</i>540–604 ). A famous bearer of the name in modern times is the film star  Gregory Peck  (  1916–2003 ). The name has traditionally been popular in Scotland, where it is often found in the form  <b>Gregor</b> ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Gregory de Rutherfurd was born about 1158, in Roxburghshire, Scotland, his father, Robert , Lord of Rodyrforde, was 40 and his mother, Mrs Robertus Dominus DeRodyrforde, was 30. He had at least 2 sons with Mrs Gregory de Rutherfurd. He died about 1214, at the age of 58."},"et":{"abt. 1158–abt. 1214":"umbes 1158–umbes 1214","1155–Male":"1155–Surnud","1158–1214":"1158–1214","1160–1200":"1160–1200","1155–